  "texts": [
    "• Constraints from pA and dA collisions Data from p/dA collisions at SPS and RHIC are primarily used to constrain the CNM effects.",
    "However, the medium assumed to be formed in d-Au reactions at RHIC has also been used to determine a nonperturbative correction to the QGP suppression rate of the ψ(2S) in terms of a phenomenological K factor of ∼2-3 multiplying its quasifree reaction rate [210].",
    "• Medium evolution model The fireball model used in the calculation is an isentropically and cylindrically expanding isotropic fireball [10,34,40,81].",
    "This expansion model reproduces the hadron spectra at thermal freezeout that are consistent with the empirically extracted light-hadron spectra (π, K, p) similar to hydro calculations.",
    "The entropy is estimated from the multiplicities of observed charged particles and assumed to be conserved during the adiabatic expansion."
